Dopamine is a key neuromodulator for the
control of striatal circuit function.
Banerjee et al. show that evoked
dopamine secretion occurs at release
hotspots that contain active zone
proteins. Munc13, Liprin-a, and RIM
cooperate to mediate vesicle priming and
release, while other known active zone
proteins are dispensable.
